1
00:00:05,630 --> 00:00:08,330
People, they may be 
very intelligent.

2
00:00:08,330 --> 00:00:12,830
[Time of Reflection]

3
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:19,240
But if that is applied
towards external things,

4
00:00:19,249 --> 00:00:26,021
it may result 
in convenience

5
00:00:26,021 --> 00:00:29,009
in terms 
of mundane activities,

6
00:00:29,009 --> 00:00:33,609
just the ordinary 
daily activities of life.

7
00:00:35,028 --> 00:00:45,400
But it perhaps would have been used 
better through internal culture

8
00:00:45,590 --> 00:00:53,319
for things that 
are substantial and lasting.

9
00:00:55,320 --> 00:01:01,611
So, and we see
this resurfacing again,

10
00:01:01,624 --> 00:01:04,051
reappearing again.

11
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:14,159
in the time of the Internet 
and so‒called ‘digital lifestyle’,

12
00:01:14,159 --> 00:01:21,119
and how much people 
are dependent upon

13
00:01:21,119 --> 00:01:23,709
electronic devices 
and such things.

14
00:01:23,709 --> 00:01:28,230
It’s not to say
that they are bad or good,

15
00:01:28,230 --> 00:01:32,439
they’re what they are,
you know, it's technology.

16
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:34,709
But we have 
a practical experience here

17
00:01:34,709 --> 00:01:40,431
that regularly
the power goes off.

18
00:01:40,741 --> 00:01:44,500
And at that time
it becomes very quiet,

19
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:51,500
and for the most part 
so many electronic devices

20
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:56,350
are... the way 
of communicating—

21
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:59,611
the Internet and the Wi-Fi—
that all goes down,

22
00:01:59,659 --> 00:02:04,339
and then it may stop 
one’s normal activities.

23
00:02:04,339 --> 00:02:08,408
And then we’ll see
it can be a test,

24
00:02:08,414 --> 00:02:16,290
if one is still capable of being calm, 
peaceful, going inward,

25
00:02:16,298 --> 00:02:19,181
spending some time 
with themselves

26
00:02:19,193 --> 00:02:24,746
or using this 
as a time of reflection.

27
00:02:24,762 --> 00:02:28,049
So, ‘simple living, high thinking’ 
means

28
00:02:28,076 --> 00:02:30,241
you can complicate 
your living 

29
00:02:30,241 --> 00:02:35,431
to the point of where 
the real purpose of life

30
00:02:35,431 --> 00:02:39,120
as indicated by Socrates
in the statement:

31
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:42,561
“The unexamined life 
is not a life worth living.”

32
00:02:42,573 --> 00:02:46,631
So it means introspection,
ātma samīkṣā—

33
00:02:46,634 --> 00:02:54,060
self‒analysis, psychoanalysis 
and literally

34
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:58,050
about the soul, understanding 
one’s spiritual identity.

35
